cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM 

The paper deals with the transmission of confidential data over wireless channels, which falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of wireless channels also suggests the involvement of networking and communication technologies (cs.NI). The paper also presents practical schemes for wireless information-theoretic security, which involves the design and implementation of systems (cs.SY) and potentially the use of multimedia technologies (cs.MM) for data transmission.
